      "content": "but i'm asking because i'm trying to avoid that slow taper thing because it's such a hassle with all the extra doctor visits. if my INR has been perfectly in the target range for months on the 5mg, isn't it basically a fact that my body is already adjusted? wouldn't just switching to 2mg be a pretty standard way to lower the concentration safely? i just want a definitive answer on whether a lower dose is clinically sound for someone in my position.",
